        <div class="about">
          <h1>What is Piclo?</h1>
          <p>Piclo is the UKâ€™s only online marketplace for renewable energy. The service gives consumers and generators direct access to each other, offering innovators a new model for buying and selling energy.</p>
          <p>For sustainable business, Piclo is a tool to make conscious and active decisions about where they source electricity from. For renewable energy generators, Piclo shows them their electricity market, and charts demand for their electricity at different price levels.</p>
          <h1>How does it work?</h1>
          <p>Renewable electricity generators set pricing and access preferences, while consumers set their electricity portfolio preferences through the online service, available on your computer, phone and tablet.</p>
          <p>Piclo takes in all the pricing and preferences information and matches electricity demand and supply every half hour - 48 times every day. Good Energy help ensure that the marketplace is always balanced, purchasing surplus power or providing 100% renewable top-up when required.</p>
          <h1>Who is behind Piclo?</h1>
          <p>Piclo is a collaboration between innovative energy startup, Open Utility, and 100% renewable energy supplier, Good Energy. We share a common vision of a world powered by renewable energy helping combat climate change.</p>
          <p>Open Utility has developed and is responsible for the software, groundbreaking electricity matching technology, and customer engagement.</p>
          <p>Good Energy is a 100% renewable electricity supplier providing Piclo with their energy trading, contracts, billing and award-winning customer service.</p>
          <p>Piclo is supported by the Energy Entrepreneurs Fund from DECC and Nominet Trust.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
